measurements.description:
Ninety six flowers and 279 buds alternately arranged on 27 pendulous lateral 7.5-cm inflorescences;
 canes terete, upright 48.5 cm long; leaves lanceolate, alternate, margins are entire;
 ovaries terete, verrucose;
 sepals narrowly obovate, verrucose on abaxial surface, yellow-orange;
 petals filamentous, curved, cream; 
 lip trilobed, orange centrally, white on margin, adnate to column, three calli,
 central callus extending to margin of lip; column bilobular, obovate, white, green basally,
 anther cap tan; substance firm; texture matte;
 light floral fragrance, recognized for educational value and rarity in cultivation.
